WHO   — The Original Cron — the first cron, shipped with 7th Edition Unix and attributed to Brian Kernighan — a simple periodic runner of a fixed job list
WHAT  — the first cron, shipped with 7th Edition Unix and attributed to Brian Kernighan — a simple periodic runner of a fixed job list
WHERE — CRN · The Cron Job — Unix scheduling, ~1975 → today (LOGISMÓS domain)  Framework inputs: cron; crontab; crond; the schedule; the box; the watch  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — It is the complete idea in crude form: before per-user tables or macros, just a process whose only job was to run other jobs on time.
HOW   — Crystallized from the history & practice of cron.

